      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "THICKSKINNED (3) won a CL1 over a mile at Launceston and then disappointed 22-days ago at Hobart in stronger than this. Has won a trial here since, and the extra metres look to suit. He can bounce back. SPRING BEAN (1) ran a much better race last start, finishing 2.75 lengths away over 2100m at Launceston. Well placed keeping the 3kg claim and can figure in the finish this time. MANHATTAN NIGHTS (4) didn't fire at odds at Hobart last time but was beaten just 1.6L over a mile there prior. Has the top hoop aboard today and she has won on the gelding. Has to be kept safe. LINDRUM (5) and MIGHTYMAXI (6) are capable enough on their day and should be around the mark.",
